The paper deals with the construction of small tree grammars and circuits, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of logarithmic space algorithms also suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the application of the results to arithmetical formulas suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
